Adding `aggregationConfigs` to enable configuring compression. 

```
"starTreeIndexConfigs": [
        {
          "dimensionsSplitOrder": [
            "a",
            "b",
            "c"
          ],
          "skipStarNodeCreationForDimensions": [],
          "functionColumnPairs": [],
          "aggregationConfigs": [
            {
              "columnName": "column1",
              "aggregationFunction": "SUM",
              "compressionCodec": "SNAPPY"
            },
            {
              "columnName": "column2",
              "aggregationFunction": "distinctcounthll",
              "compressionCodec": "LZ4"
            }
          ],
          "maxLeafRecords": 10000
        }
      ]
```

See: https://github.com/apache/pinot/issues/9694

This change was tested manually with multiple segment refresh on `DOUBLE` and `BYTES` metrics columns.

This PR adds a new interface and it's implementation for existing forward index readers, that allows a caller to get exact set of buffer byte ranges that are accessed internally when reading a given docId. This information can be used to support prefetching of exact byte ranges during query processing if the list of docIds to be fetched is known beforehand, and the buffer type supports selective prefetching of data.

The newly added methods provide a way for users to get exact byte ranges that are fetched when accessing a given docId. Eg

```
// buffer that represents myColumn's fwd index
PinotDataBuffer dataBuffer = segmentReader.getIndexFor("myColumn", StandardIndexes.forward());

// Creating forward index reader
ForwardIndexReader reader = ForwardIndexReaderFactory.createIndexReader(dataBuffer, segmentMetadata.getColumnMetadataFor("myColumn"));

// Reader allows fetching docId -> ByteRange information
if (reader.isBufferByteRangeInfoSupported()) {
    if (reader.isFixedOffsetMappingType()) {
        // Buffer has a fixed docId -> byte range mapping
        int docId = 0;
        long offsetForDocId = reader.getRawDataStartOffset() + reader.getDocLength() * docId;
        int sizeForDocId = reader.getDocLength();
    } else {
        // The buffer layout doesn't have a fixed docId -> byte range mapping
        int docId = 0;
        List<ByteRanges> ranges = new ArrayList<>();
        reader.recordDocIdByteRanges(docId, reader.createContext(), ranges);
        // ranges list now has all the byte ranges that were accessed when reading the given docId
    }
}
```

- Expose `invalidRealtimeRowsDropped` to measure decoding errors in stream.
- Expose `incompleteRealtimeRowsConsumed` to measure transformation errors when `continueOnError` has been set to true.
- Expose `rowsWithErrors` to cover any error while processing a row (catch-all, covers both the cases above).

